â¡ï¸Attributes are optional; you can use them to provide additional information about an HTML element.
â¡ï¸Attributes have name and value pairs, but some of the attributes do not require any value; those are known as Boolean attributes.
â¡ï¸An HTML element can have multiple attributes, and they should be separated by spaces.
â¡ï¸Attributes should always be written with the opening tag.
â¡ï¸All HTML elements can have attributes except a few like <head>, <title>, <script>, etc.
â¡ï¸W3C recommends using attributes in lowercase and keeping the value in quotes.

